    - penalty_clauses - penalty_clauses:
  enforceability_level: PROHIBITED
  summary: >
    Colorado courts do not enforce contractual penalty clauses. If a provision
    imposes damages that are disproportionate to anticipated harm and intended
    to punish breach rather than compensate for loss, it is an unenforceable
    penalty.
  authority:
    case_law:
      - name: Board of County Commissioners v. City & County of Denver
        citation: 40 P.3d 25 (Colo. App. 2001)
        principle: Penalty clauses are void; only reasonable liquidated damages are enforceable
  sources:
    - https://law.justia.com/cases/colorado/court-of-appeals/2001/00ca0581.html
